{{main|Somali Civil War|Disarmament in Somalia}}
The '''Conference on National Reconciliation in Somalia''' was an attempt to end the [[Somali Civil War]]. It led to the signing of the '''[[Addis Ababa Agreement (1993)]]''', on March 27, 1993. Fifteen different warring factions agreed to the principles of [[Disarmament in Somalia|reconciliation and disarmament]], but the agreement was shoaled by continued violence in Somalia. It was preceded by the [[Informal Preparatory Meeting on National Reconciliation]].
