The '''Human Rights Law Alliance''' (HRLA) is a body associated with the [[Australian Christian Lobby]] (ACL) focussing on what are stated as freedoms neglected by the [[Australian Human Rights Commission]], such as: 'freedom of speech, freedom of religion, freedom of conscience and freedom of association'.<ref>[http://www.theaustralian.com.au/business/legal-affairs/human-rights-law-alliance-formed-to-fight-for-essential-freedoms/news-story/2fdc1a2b046d5322d2e08c5226a2cf09 Chris Merritt, (2 September 2016), Human Rights Law Alliance formed to fight for essential freedoms, ''The Australian'']. Retrieved 17 September 2017</ref> Seed funding was provided by the ACL.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://acl.nationbuilder.com/donate_hrla |title=Help Take Our Fight To Uphold Christian Values To The Next Level |accessdate=2017-09-17 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112172750/https://acl.nationbuilder.com/donate_hrla |archivedate=12 November 2016 |df= }}</ref>
As of October 2018, the official web site is no longer active.
==Campaigns and cases== The HRLA is active in the campaign against [[same sex marriage]] in Australia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/federal-politics/political-news/christian-fighting-fund-to-bankroll-legal-action-for-samesex-marriage-objectors-20161005-grw1mx.html |title=Christian fighting fund to bankroll legal action for same-sex marriage objectors |author= Koziol, Michael |date=6 October 2016|work=[[Sydney Morning Herald]]|accessdate=21 November 2017}}</ref>
Jointly with the ACL, HRLA lodged a submission to the Australian Senate Select Committee on the 'Exposure Draft Of The Marriage Amendment (Same-Sex Marriage)' Bill.<ref>[http://www.aph.gov.au/DocumentStore.ashx?id=411661c0-6f9e-4aee-ab53-ed7ef037e525&subId=462658 Submission No. 67 from the Human Rights Law Alliance and Australian Christian Lobby to the Australian Senate Select Committee on The Exposure Draft Of The Marriage Amendment (Same-Sex Marriage) Bill.]. Retrieved 17 September 2017</ref>
